Group_Field_Binary.name: Downlink PN Ranging Phase CHDO (Data Type 5)
Group_Field_Binary.description: Downlink PN Ranging Phase CHDO (Data Type 5)

Field_Binary.name: chdo_type
Field_Binary.description: Type attribute of the downlink PN ranging phase data CHDO. Set to 10 because this CHDO contains binary data.

Field_Binary.name: chdo_length
Field_Binary.description: Length attribute of the downlink PN ranging phase data CHDO value field. Number of bytes after this item. Set to 258.

Field_Binary.name: stn_cal
Field_Binary.description: Station calibration value. (Two-way). Value includes the equipment in the path, but not the Z-height correction. Values 0.0 to 1.8e5; value 0.0 indicates not measured. One range unit (RU) = (exc_scalar_den/exc_scalar_num)/(16*FRQ_UP) where FRQ_UP is the uplink carrier frequency and the two scalars are given in fields 56 and 57. Range is measured in RU to give a stable reference when the uplink is being ramped.

Field_Binary.name: dl_stn_cal
Field_Binary.description: Downlink station calibration value. Value includes the downlink equipment in the path, but not the Z-height correction. Values 0.0 to 1.8e5; value 0.0 indicates not measured. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: dl_cal_freq
Field_Binary.description: Downlink calibration frequency -- frequency at which the calibration was done. Values 2.2e9 to 32.3e9 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: cal_std_dev
Field_Binary.description: Standard deviation of station calibration value. Applies to stn_cal (field 3) and dl_stn_cal (field 4). Values 0.0 to 1.8e5 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: cal_pts
Field_Binary.description: Calibration points -- number of measurements made in computing station calibration values. Applies to stn_cal (field 3), dl_stn_cal (field 4), and cal_std_dev (field 6). Values 0 to 65535 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: dl_rng_phs
Field_Binary.description: Measured range phase. Values 0.0 to 2**30 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: figure_merit
Field_Binary.description: Probability of Acquistion (formerly called Figure of Merit). The probability of acquiring the correct range. Values 0.0 to 100.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rng_resid
Field_Binary.description: Range residual -- measured range minus predicted range. Values -2**30 to 2**30 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: drvid
Field_Binary.description: Differenced range versus integrated Dopper (DRVID), measured using phase data from carrier. Values -2**30 to 2**30 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: rtlt
Field_Binary.description: Predicted round trip light time. Values 0.0 to 86400.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: pcn0
Field_Binary.description: Ratio of carrier power (Pc) to noise power spectral density (N0). Values 0.0 to 90.0 are allowed; value -300.0 indicates no signal.

Field_Binary.name: pcn0_resid
Field_Binary.description: Pc/N0 residual -- actual value minus predicted value. Values -90.0 to 90.0 are allowed; value -300.0 indicates no signal or that the carrier is suppressed.

Field_Binary.name: pdn0
Field_Binary.description: Ratio of data power (Pd) to noise power spectral density (N0). Values 0.0 to 90.0 are allowed; value -300.0 indicates no signal.

Field_Binary.name: pdn0_resid
Field_Binary.description: Pd/N0 residual -- actual value minus predicted value. Values -90.0 to 90.0 are allowed; value -300.0 indicates no signal.

Field_Binary.name: prn0
Field_Binary.description: Ratio of ranging power (Pr) to noise power spectral density (N0). Values -10.0 to 90.0 are allowed; value -300.0 indcates no signal.

Field_Binary.name: prn0_resid
Field_Binary.description: Pr/N0 residual -- actual value minus predicted value. Values -90.0 to 90.0 are allowed; value -300.0 indicates no signal.

Field_Binary.name: rcv_inphs_time_year
Field_Binary.description: Receive In-phase time -- year. Year of the time of zero phase on downlink range signal correlation. Values 1958 to 3000 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rcv_inphs_time_doy
Field_Binary.description: Receive In-phase time -- day of year. Day of year of the time of zero phase on downlink range signal correlation. Values 1 to 366 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rcv_inphs_time_sec
Field_Binary.description: Receive In-phase time -- seconds of day. Seconds of day of the time of zero phase on downlink range generation. Values 0.0 to 86400.999999 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: exc_scalar_num
Field_Binary.description: Exciter Scalar Numerator. Numerator of ratio between ranging reference signal and uplink sky frequency. Values 1 to 2**32-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: exc_scalar_den
Field_Binary.description: Exciter Scalar Denominator. Denominator of ratio between ranging reference signal and uplink sky frequency. values 1 ro 2**32-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rng_cycle_time
Field_Binary.description: Ranging cycle time -- integration time for each PN range point. Values 1.0 to 1.0e5 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: inphs_correl
Field_Binary.description: The in-phase value of the clock component correlation. Values -1.000e8 to 1.000e8 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: quad_phs_correl
Field_Binary.description: The quadrature phase value of the clock component correlation. Values -1.000e8 to 1.000e8 are allowed.
